  "id": "MGASA-2019-0103",
  "summary": "Updated gnutls packages fix security vulnerability",
  "details": "A Bleichenbacher type side-channel based padding oracle attack was found\nin the way gnutls handles verification of RSA decrypted PKCS#1 v1.5 data.\nAn attacker who is able to run process on the same physical core as the\nvictim process, could use this to extract plaintext or in some cases\ndowngrade any TLS connections to a vulnerable server. (CVE-2018-16868)\n",
